<task id="008" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D1-08 Telemetry events + cost observability for R5 Summarize-for-Chat</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort></actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started></started>
    <completed></completed>
    <phase>Phase 1 — Platform Extensions</phase>
    <wave>P1-G5 (parallel-safe with 007; independent of 009)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>none (downstream Phase 3 D3-03 dashboards consume these events)</dependencies>
    <tags>bff, telemetry, observability, cost</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Instrument the R5 Summarize-for-Chat vertical slice with telemetry that supports
    cost observability + downstream Phase 3 dashboards (D3-03). Emit a single
    canonical event `r5.summarize.invocation` from BOTH invocation paths — the
    agent-tool path (`InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` registered on `SprkChatAgent`)
    AND the direct endpoint path (`POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize`) —
    with the same property schema so dashboards can compare path mix. Add a
    per-session `spaarke-session-files` index document-count metric so cost +
    eviction behavior is queryable from App Insights / Kusto.

    Constraints binding on this task:
    1. REUSE existing telemetry framework — `AiTelemetry` (Meter
       `Sprk.Bff.Api.Ai`, OpenTelemetry Counter / Histogram primitives) is the
       canonical surface for AI metrics. DO NOT introduce a new framework (no
       ApplicationInsights `TelemetryClient` direct use; OpenTelemetry meter +
       structured `ILogger` is the established pattern per `AiTelemetry.cs` /
       `RagTelemetry.cs`).
    2. Event-name "r5.summarize.invocation" is exact (kebab-case dotted; matches
       the established `ai.summarize.*` / `rag.search.*` family).
    3. Cardinality discipline — properties have BOUNDED cardinality. `path` is
       an enum of two literals (`agent_tool` | `direct_endpoint`);
       `completion_status` is an enum (`success` | `failed` | `declined` |
       `cancelled`); `file_count` and `total_tokens` and `latency_ms` are
       numerics. NEVER include free-form user input, document content, file
       names, session IDs, or correlation IDs as event-property dimensions
       (correlation IDs go on the Activity / span context, not as a metric
       dimension — they explode cardinality and don't fit App Insights metric
       store).
    4. NO new feature flags (per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 + ADR-018).
    5. DI registration (if needed at all — `AiTelemetry` is already
       singleton-registered) goes inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` per ADR-010.
       Zero new top-level `Program.cs` lines.
    6. BFF publish-size: per-task verification mandatory (R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6).
       Expected delta ~0 MB (no new packages; reuses existing OpenTelemetry).

    Why the schema must be stable: Phase 3 task 042 (D3-03 dashboards) writes
    Kusto queries against these exact property names. A schema breaking change
    later would invalidate the dashboards. Treat the event schema like a
    public-API surface from this commit forward.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET observability engineer with deep experience in OpenTelemetry
    Meters + Counters + Histograms, Application Insights / Kusto querying, and
    cardinality discipline for production metric stores. Familiar with the
    `AiTelemetry` / `RagTelemetry` patterns already in Sprk.Bff.Api.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new `R5SummarizeTelemetry` class (sibling to `AiTelemetry` /
    `RagTelemetry`) ships in
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/R5SummarizeTelemetry.cs`. It emits
    one canonical event `r5.summarize.invocation` (Counter) with bounded
    dimensions `path`, `completion_status` and three Histograms tracking
    `file_count`, `total_tokens`, `latency_ms` keyed by those same dimensions.
    It also emits a Histogram `r5.session_files.index_size` (per-session
    document count, observed at write-time or eviction-time, dimension =
    `phase` ∈ {`post_write` | `post_evict` | `post_cleanup`}). Both invocation
    code paths (`InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` agent-tool handler AND the direct
    `SummarizeSessionEndpoint`) call the SAME telemetry method with their
    respective `path` literal so dashboards see a single coherent event stream.
    `R5SummarizeTelemetry` is singleton-registered inside `AnalysisServicesModule`
    (per ADR-010), and its Meter (`Sprk.Bff.Api.R5Summarize`) is wired into
    `TelemetryModule.AddTelemetryModule()` `AddMeter(...)`. Unit tests verify the
    expected event shape using OpenTelemetry's `MeterListener` / in-process
    metric capture pattern. The schema is documented in XML doc-comments on
    every method and is stable for downstream D3-03 consumption.
  </goal>

