    <file purpose="canonical-telemetry-pattern-rag">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/RagTelemetry.cs</file>
    <file purpose="meter-registration-site">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/TelemetryModule.cs</file>
    <file purpose="di-registration-site">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="bff-extensions-constraints">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate">MUST reuse the established OpenTelemetry `Meter` + `Counter&lt;long&gt;` + `Histogram&lt;double&gt;` / `Histogram&lt;long&gt;` pattern from `AiTelemetry.cs` / `RagTelemetry.cs`. MUST NOT introduce `Microsoft.ApplicationInsights.TelemetryClient` direct usage or any other parallel telemetry framework.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2">NO new feature flags. `R5SummarizeTelemetry` is unconditionally registered.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.3 + ADR-010">All registrations inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`. Meter wiring inside `TelemetryModule.cs`. ZERO new top-level `Program.cs` lines.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 + ADR-029 + CLAUDE.md §10">Per-task BFF publish-size verification mandatory. Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`, measure compressed output, report absolute + delta vs baseline (~45.65 MB). Expected delta ≈ 0 MB; ≥+5 MB single-task delta requires escalation.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Tenant isolation — `tenantId` dimension MAY be added per the `RagTelemetry.RecordRagSearchSuccess` precedent (low cardinality given tenant count). `sessionId` MUST NOT be a metric dimension (high cardinality; goes on the Activity / span only).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Telemetry MUST NOT include document content, file contents, prompt text, or any other PII / customer data as metric dimensions or log structured fields. Only enums, counts, durations, and tenantId (the existing low-cardinality dimension).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline">R5 introduces no new flags. `R5SummarizeTelemetry` is unconditionally registered (no Null-Object kill-switch coverage needed per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">No PaneEventBus changes in this task — telemetry is BFF-side OpenTelemetry only. Out of scope: frontend instrumentation.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-06 cost control">Token counts (`total_tokens`) emitted via Histogram so per-session token-budget consumption is queryable. Cost dashboards (D3-03) derive cost-per-session from this Histogram + the existing token-pricing constants.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-13">No new HIGH-severity CVEs introduced by this task. Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` on `Sprk.Bff.Api` after build; verify clean. Expected to be a no-op (no new packages).</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 bff-extensions Placement Justification">Telemetry placement: BELONGS in BFF. Justification: instrumentation is intrinsic to the operations being measured (chat-tool dispatch + endpoint handling) and cannot be cleanly extracted into a sidecar. Telemetry layer additions consume zero meaningful publish-size budget. Decision criteria from `bff-extensions.md` satisfied: not a stateless utility; tightly coupled to BFF request lifecycle.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project — cardinality discipline (BINDING)">Event dimensions: `path` enum of 2 literals, `completion_status` enum of 4 literals, `tenantId` (low-cardinality dimension following `RagTelemetry` precedent). NO `sessionId`, NO correlation IDs, NO user IDs, NO file names, NO prompts, NO model names as dimensions on the main invocation event (model name CAN appear on the existing `ai.summarize.tokens` AiTelemetry counter per existing precedent if needed — but R5 reuses that existing counter rather than duplicating).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project — schema stability">Property names + types of `r5.summarize.invocation` MUST be treated as a stable downstream contract from this commit. Phase 3 task 042 (D3-03 dashboards) writes Kusto queries against these names. Renames after this task ship require coordinated dashboard updates.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>opentelemetry/dotnet-metrics + structured-logging-conventions</topic>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/AiTelemetry.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/RagTelemetry.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/AiLatencyTelemetry.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/TelemetryModule.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-014-ai-caching-tenant-isolation.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="OpenTelemetry Meter + Counter + Histogram singleton" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/AiTelemetry.cs">
        Mirror this exact pattern: private `Meter _meter` field, private
        `Counter&lt;long&gt;` / `Histogram&lt;double&gt;` / `Histogram&lt;long&gt;` instruments,
        `MeterName` const, static `ActivitySource` for distributed tracing,
        `Dispose()` releases the meter. Public record-* methods accept the
        bounded dimensions as method parameters (NOT as `params object[]`
        property bags). This forces cardinality discipline at the call site.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Tag list construction with bounded dimensions" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/RagTelemetry.cs">
        Use `TagList` with explicit kvp adds. Pattern: `{ "status", success ?
        "success" : "failed" }` for status enums; conditional `tags.Add(...)`
        for optional dimensions like `tenantId`. NEVER concatenate user input
        into tag values.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Meter registration in TelemetryModule" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/TelemetryModule.cs">
        `services.AddOpenTelemetry().WithMetrics(m =&gt; m.AddMeter("Sprk.Bff.Api.R5Summarize"))`
        — add the new Meter name to the existing list (lines 22–32). Match the
        existing comment style (one comment per added meter explaining purpose).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="DI registration alongside AiTelemetry" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs">
        `services.AddSingleton&lt;AiTelemetry&gt;()` on line 25 is the precedent.
        Register `R5SummarizeTelemetry` as a sibling singleton in the same
        method (unconditional — it does NOT require `analysisEnabled` because
        kill-switch coverage is via `NullSprkChatAgentFactory` per R5 §3.2;
        the telemetry surface itself is harmless when unused).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Call-site instrumentation (placeholder for downstream tasks)" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs">
        Downstream task 014 (D2-04 endpoint) + 015 (D2-05 agent tool) will INJECT
        `R5SummarizeTelemetry` and call its record-* methods at completion of
        each invocation. Task 008 (THIS task) creates the class + DI wiring +
        unit tests; it does NOT modify the (not-yet-existing in this branch)
        endpoint or tool handler. The class is ready-to-consume when 012/014/015
        ship.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 ships a chat-driven "Summarize a Document" vertical slice invocable
      from two paths: (a) `/summarize` slash command → direct endpoint, (b)
      natural-language prompt → LLM tool-call → `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool`.
      Both paths converge on `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (task 012). For
      cost observability, dashboards (Phase 3 task 042 / D3-03) need to see
      the path mix, file_count distribution, token consumption, and latency
      distribution as a single coherent event stream — not two parallel event
      streams from two parallel code paths. This task ships the canonical
      `r5.summarize.invocation` event + the session-files index-size metric
      with the schema locked from day one.

      Additionally, per spec NFR-06 (cost control) and Phase 3 D3-03 (cost
      dashboards), this task surfaces per-session token-budget consumption so
      operations can monitor budget burn-down + tune the existing
      `AgentCostControlMiddleware` defaults (10K tokens per session).

      The session-files index-size metric (`r5.session_files.index_size`)
      supports the cleanup-job tuning question from spec NFR-02 (assumed 6h
      cleanup cadence; may tune to 1h if storage grows). Without this metric
      the tuning decision is blind.
    </background>
    <dependencies></dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>`AiTelemetry.RecordTokenUsage` / `RecordSuccess` — existing
        precedent for token + duration histograms; R5 telemetry is additive on
        a NEW Meter to keep R5-specific dashboards trivially filterable by
        meter name without polluting the broader `ai.summarize.*` family.</item>
      <item>Task 007 (D1-07 session-files cleanup `IHostedService`) writes the
        eviction-count metric; this task defines the `r5.session_files.index_size`
        Histogram that 007's cleanup job will record into post-eviction. Both
        tasks are in P1-G5 + parallel-safe; 007 will reference the histogram
        method signature this task exposes.</item>
      <item>Task 014 (D2-04 direct endpoint) + Task 015 (D2-05 agent tool) will
        INJECT `R5SummarizeTelemetry` and call its record method on completion.
        This task creates the surface those downstream tasks consume.</item>
      <item>Phase 3 Task 042 (D3-03) authors the App Insights / Kusto dashboards
        that query these events. Schema stability from this commit forward is
        a downstream contract.</item>
      <item>`RagTelemetry.RecordRagSearchSuccess` includes `tenantId` as a
        low-cardinality dimension per ADR-014 — R5 follows that precedent on
        the invocation event.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

