    <step order="3" name="Plan Implementation">
      Confirm placement decision per CLAUDE.md §10 Placement Justification:
      telemetry instrumentation belongs in BFF (justification documented in
      `&lt;constraints&gt;`). List the deliverables:
      - NEW file `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/R5SummarizeTelemetry.cs`
      - EDIT `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/TelemetryModule.cs`
        (add Meter to `AddOpenTelemetry().WithMetrics(...)` list + tracing
        source)
      - EDIT `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs`
        (add `services.AddSingleton&lt;R5SummarizeTelemetry&gt;()` alongside the
        existing AiTelemetry singleton)
      - NEW test file
        `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Telemetry/R5SummarizeTelemetryTests.cs`

      Lock the event schema (write down BEFORE coding, treat as contract):

      | Instrument | Type | Dimensions (BOUNDED) |
      |---|---|---|
      | `r5.summarize.invocation` | `Counter&lt;long&gt;` | `path` (enum: `agent_tool` \| `direct_endpoint`), `completion_status` (enum: `success` \| `failed` \| `declined` \| `cancelled`), `tenantId` (low-cardinality) |
      | `r5.summarize.file_count` | `Histogram&lt;long&gt;` | same as above |
      | `r5.summarize.total_tokens` | `Histogram&lt;long&gt;` | same as above |
      | `r5.summarize.latency_ms` | `Histogram&lt;double&gt;` | same as above |
      | `r5.session_files.index_size` | `Histogram&lt;long&gt;` | `phase` (enum: `post_write` \| `post_evict` \| `post_cleanup`), `tenantId` |

      Confirm no other dimensions. Record schema in XML doc-comments on the
      class + each method.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement R5SummarizeTelemetry class">
      Create
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/R5SummarizeTelemetry.cs`
      following the `AiTelemetry.cs` structural template exactly:
      - `namespace Sprk.Bff.Api.Telemetry;`
      - XML doc-comment header documenting purpose + meter name + canonical
        App Insights / Kusto queries (mirror lines 7–19 of AiTelemetry.cs)
      - Private `Meter _meter` + `MeterName = "Sprk.Bff.Api.R5Summarize"`
        + public static `ActivitySource`
      - Private instruments (one per row in the schema table above)
      - Constructor creates Meter + instruments with `name`, `unit`,
        `description` triples following the AiTelemetry style
      - Public `RecordSummarizeInvocation(string path, string completionStatus,
        long fileCount, long totalTokens, double latencyMs, string? tenantId
        = null)` method — accepts `path` and `completionStatus` as STRING
        ENUMS (validated against private `static readonly` HashSet&lt;string&gt;
        whitelists; throw ArgumentException on out-of-enum input — this is
        the cardinality safety mechanism)
      - Public `RecordSessionFilesIndexSize(string phase, long documentCount,
        string? tenantId = null)` method — same enum-validation discipline
        for `phase`
      - `Dispose()` releases the meter
      - XML doc-comments on every public method specifying parameters + enum
        valid values + the dimension set treated as the downstream contract

      Add private `static readonly` HashSets:
      ```csharp
      private static readonly HashSet&lt;string&gt; ValidPaths = new() { "agent_tool", "direct_endpoint" };
      private static readonly HashSet&lt;string&gt; ValidStatuses = new() { "success", "failed", "declined", "cancelled" };
      private static readonly HashSet&lt;string&gt; ValidPhases = new() { "post_write", "post_evict", "post_cleanup" };
      ```
      These are the cardinality enforcement mechanism — invalid input throws
      at the call site (loud failure during development) rather than silently
      polluting the metric store with high-cardinality dimensions in production.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Wire Meter into TelemetryModule">
      Edit `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/TelemetryModule.cs`:
      - In the `metrics.AddMeter(...)` block (currently lines 22–32), ADD:
        ```csharp
        // R5 Summarize meter (D1-08): r5.summarize.invocation + r5.session_files.index_size
        metrics.AddMeter("Sprk.Bff.Api.R5Summarize");
        ```
      - In the `tracing.AddSource(...)` block (currently lines 36–38), ADD:
        ```csharp
        tracing.AddSource("Sprk.Bff.Api.R5Summarize");
        ```
      Confirm zero new top-level `Program.cs` lines.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Register R5SummarizeTelemetry in AnalysisServicesModule">
      Edit
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs`:
      Add `services.AddSingleton&lt;Sprk.Bff.Api.Telemetry.R5SummarizeTelemetry&gt;();`
      adjacent to the existing `services.AddSingleton&lt;Sprk.Bff.Api.Telemetry.
      AiTelemetry&gt;();` registration (line 25). Place it UNCONDITIONALLY (NOT
      inside the `if (analysisEnabled && documentIntelligenceEnabled)` block)
      because telemetry-class registration is harmless when not invoked and
      reduces conditional-registration risk per CLAUDE.md §10 F.1
      (Asymmetric-Registration anti-pattern).
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Build + verify compilation">
      Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Confirm zero new
      compiler warnings + zero new compiler errors. Confirm the new
      `R5SummarizeTelemetry` resolves via DI by running a quick startup
      smoke (`dotnet run` against the Sprk.Bff.Api project locally for a few
      seconds → verify no DI resolution errors at `WebApplication.Build()`).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Write unit tests">
      Create
      `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Telemetry/R5SummarizeTelemetryTests.cs`
      with these test cases:
      - `RecordSummarizeInvocation_WithValidEnums_EmitsExpectedCounter` —
        uses OpenTelemetry's `MeterListener` API to capture emitted
